The Kebbi State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) has distributed relief materials to 400 Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) who were displaced as a result of flood and bandits’ attacks in the state. The Acting Executive Secretary of the Agency, Rabi’u Kamba, made this known on Tuesday in Birnin Kebbi. According to him, the N2 million-worth relief items distributed included rice, beans, maize, millet, salt, detergent, vegetable oil and yams. The secretary told the beneficiaries that the gesture was to cushion the effect of the disaster that befell them. Benue to close IDP camps soon Saudi Arabian centre distributes relief materials to Yobe IDPs Hoodlums allegedly set Cross River SEMA office on fire, destroy relief materials